#: ../../source/deploy/mobile/secure-mobile-file-storage.rst:7
msgid ""
"This document outlines the security measures governing file storage in "
"the Mattermost mobile app for iOS and Android. It describes how files are"
" stored, accessed, and protected within the application container, "
"addressing concerns related to sensitive data—including Controlled "
"Unclassified Information (CUI) and HIPAA-regulated data—on mobile "
"devices. The objective is to ensure that only authorized personnel can "
"view, access, or share such data while preventing exposure to "
"unauthorized parties and ensuring isolation from third-party "
"applications."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deploy/mobile/secure-mobile-file-storage.rst:9
msgid ""
"Mattermost leverages robust sandboxing mechanisms on both iOS and Android"
" to securely store files in its cache folder within the application "
"container, ensuring isolation from unauthorized third-party apps. User-"
"initiated actions (download, share, copy link) are controlled by server-"
"side permissions, allowing administrators to restrict access to sensitive"
" data like CUI or HIPAA-regulated information to authorized personnel "
"only."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deploy/mobile/secure-mobile-file-storage.rst:12
msgid "File storage and app sandbox security"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deploy/mobile/secure-mobile-file-storage.rst:14
msgid ""
"Files uploaded or accessed via the Mattermost mobile app are stored in "
"the app’s cache folder, which resides within the app’s private storage "
"container. This storage location is isolated by each platform’s "
"sandboxing model:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deploy/mobile/secure-mobile-file-storage.rst:17
msgid "iOS – app sandbox"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deploy/mobile/secure-mobile-file-storage.rst:19
#: ../../source/deploy/mobile/secure-mobile-file-storage.rst:38
msgid "**Sandboxing & storage:**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deploy/mobile/secure-mobile-file-storage.rst:21
msgid ""
"iOS employs a rigorous sandboxing model that relies on containerized file"
" systems and strict process isolation. Each app operates within its own "
"sandbox, with its home directory randomly assigned during installation. "
"As a result, files stored within the Mattermost app’s cache folder remain"
" accessible only to the app unless explicitly shared by the user."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deploy/mobile/secure-mobile-file-storage.rst:23
#: ../../source/deploy/mobile/secure-mobile-file-storage.rst:42
msgid "**Secure file viewing:**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deploy/mobile/secure-mobile-file-storage.rst:25
msgid ""
"Non-image and non-video files are rendered using secure frameworks such "
"as QLPreviewController. This controller displays file previews within the"
" app’s sandbox, ensuring that raw file data isn’t exposed to external "
"processes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deploy/mobile/secure-mobile-file-storage.rst:26
msgid ""
"Supported image and video files are previewed directly within the app, "
"with the files downloaded to the app's cache folder located within its "
"secure sandbox. For unsupported image and video formats, the Mattermost "
"mobile app uses the QLPreviewController framework, just as it does for "
"other file types."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deploy/mobile/secure-mobile-file-storage.rst:27
msgid ""
"If the file format is also unsupported by QLPreviewController and "
":ref:`mobile downloads are enabled <configure/site-configuration-"
"settings:allow file downloads on mobile>` on the server, users can "
"download the file to a location of their choosing. However, if mobile "
"downloads are disabled, these files become unavailable to the user."
